    "last_activity_date" : 1603424972,
    "last_edit_date" : 1603424972,
    "creation_date" : 1600824388,
    "answer_id" : 64019725,
    "question_id" : 60362018,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Existing answers are great, and they work.</p>\n<p>But an easier solution is to open the terminal and run this:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-sh prettyprint-override\"><code>xattr -d com.apple.quarantine $(which chromedriver)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12197766,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 8902859,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-xN6Q9tMbg-Y/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAFis/6eoRk2QuZFU/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Kevin Hu",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8902859/kevin-hu"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1601483910,
    "creation_date" : 1601483910,
    "answer_id" : 64142025,
    "question_id" : 60362018,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>xattr -d com.apple.quarantine $(which chromedriver)</code> alone is not enough.</p>\n<p>with the lastest version of chromedriver, it seem like they are dividing into version folders.<br />\nfor me on 9/30/20. what worked for me is <code>xattr -d com.apple.quarantine 85.0.4183.87/chromedriver</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18983025,
      "reputation" : 369,
      "user_id" : 13854030,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgaEk-9rADvIzOMoRHXhv7sVdZAZuLYIWkD4N5f=k-s256",
      "display_name" : "Shubhanker Singh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13854030/shubhanker-singh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 26,
    "last_activity_date" : 1622451888,
    "last_edit_date" : 1622451888,
    "creation_date" : 1608591056,
    "answer_id" : 65401026,
    "question_id" : 60362018,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Two steps to solve this:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to the path using command- <code>cd /usr/local/bin</code> . This is where you will see your chromedriver installed.</li>\n<li>When inside the bin directory, run this command- <code>xattr -d com.apple.quarantine chromedriver</code> .</li>\n</ol>\n<p>And that's all. It worked for me like that.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 13580905,
        "reputation" : 2136,
        "user_id" : 9796935,
