    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1640891740,
    "creation_date" : 1640891740,
    "answer_id" : 70535793,
    "question_id" : 60362018,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've found that if you've tried this solution:</p>\n<pre><code>// Get the path to chromedriver, example: /usr/local/bin/chromedriver\nwhich chromedriver \n\n// Change permissions\nxattr -d com.apple.quarantine &lt;path_to_chromedriver&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>and your browser opens and then immediately closes, it could be from installing the wrong chromedriver version.</p>\n<p>Look for your chrome version by launching chrome then selecting</p>\n<pre><code>Chrome &gt; About Google Chrome\n</code></pre>\n<p>Remove your current chromedriver and search for the chromedriver that matches your chrome version displayed in your &quot;About Google Chrome&quot; (example: 96.0.4664.110). This worked for me on a mac with the Monterey OS</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4265336,
      "reputation" : 111,
      "user_id" : 3488589,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9a46f01a721fa838e225c77b2bf9992b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Thendz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3488589/thendz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1644760422,
    "creation_date" : 1644760422,
    "answer_id" : 71101310,
    "question_id" : 60362018,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The easiest way to solve this error, please follow the steps below.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to where your chrome driver application is saved / downloaded</li>\n<li>Right click and select Open with</li>\n<li>Select open with Terminal</li>\n<li>Allow or select yes</li>\n<li>you should get a success message on the terminal screen</li>\n<li>Go back to open your chrome driver or on your IDE and run, you should not get the error anymore</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
